author: Silvia Ascarelli
title: Video: Typhoon Soudelor was strong enough to lift this 747 cargo jet
text:
When Typhoon Soudelor hit Taiwan and China this weekend, it did the usual things a powerful storm does â€” uproot trees, take down power lines, drench the area with rain, even kill people.
But it also was strong enough to lift this cargo jet at an airport in Taiwan:
The Weather Channel reported the typhoon dumped 52.23 inches of rain over 72 hours in one spot in Taiwan. Winds at Taoyuan International Airport near Taipei hit 93 mph.
The typhoon killed at least eight people in Taiwan and 26 in China.
